[St Louis encephalitis virus (SLEV) is a flavivirus endemic in the USA
closely related to West Nile virus. SLEV is transmitted from wild birds to
humans by _Culex_ mosquitoes, and causes sporadic outbreaks and scattered
individual cases.

A map showing the location of Lubbock county in north western Texas can be
accessed at <http://geology.com/county-map/texas.shtml>. A
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of Texas in
south central USA can be accessed at <http://healthmap.org/r/0dcp>. - Mod.TY]
